<br>
However, the kids would have to first be taught about drug use, in order to learn it was illegal.  The kids would have to learn something was bad, before knowing it was.<br>
<br>
Dad going outside smoking, is Dad doing Dad's thing.  Not much different than Dad that goes outside to have a pipe in the morning and at night, he doesn't smoke inside because Mamma doesn't like it.  <br>
<br>
What will be important, is education and honesty from the offending parent as the children get older.  In many ways, this could put the parent in a better position of coaching away from more dangerous influences. <br>
<br>
If I had a choice between children who smoked pot, and children who drank alcholhal, I'd prefer my kids smoke pot. With exception too the fact that they could go to jail, the end result would be much more favorable provided they didn't get caught. <br>
<br>
2 glasses of Wine a days is actually recommended by the Heart association.  <br>
<br>
Most casual pot smokers don't smoke joints, because it's an incredible waste of weed. Most of us use water pipes, or regualr pipes.  The reason I bring this up is because Sapiens metions amount consumed.  The example given would consume the equivalent of 1 cigarette every 2 days by smoking at this rate. <br>
<br>
Less than a carton a year.<br>
<br>
Wulf is right, cops don;t really go after the casual user.  In fact, if you are nice, polite, and mind yourself, you'll probobly just get in confiscated, if even that.  I've known people in sitations where cops were called to break up a fight a t a party.  When they got there, cop spots the bong in the corner &quot;Nice Bong&quot; he says, and they leave it at that.<br>
<br>
This is what is so frustrating.  Most people accept that pot is not really that dangerous of a substance.  Hell law enforcement agents even admit this; yet because of those money grubbing bastards in office, good people get labeled as bad for doing something that is no worse than what others do.<br>
----<br>
<br>
Let's say our hero is not married.  He's single, owns his own company (ice cream store) and chain smokes pot all day long.  <br>
<br>
He should go to jail?<br>
<br>
Jails are overcrowded.  We let rapists, murderers, robbers, all out early!  Simply because we don't have room for them because we're filling up prisons (70%) with non-violant drug related crimes. <br>
<br>
The United States; &quot;The land of the Free&quot; Incarcerates more people than any other country in the world. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18533>Sister Maddie Faye</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ufishbeak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fishbeak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/18/02 2:04:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should this man go to jail?</span><hr size=1> All valid points Maddie.<br>
